item.title: Blog Post Title
item.dc:creator: 1gufxz
item.content:encoded:
What goes into a blog post? Helpful, industry-specific content that: 1) gives readers a useful takeaway, and 2) shows you're an industry expert.
Use your company's blog posts to opine on current industry topics, humanize your company, and show how your products and services can help people.

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: 1gufxz
item.content:encoded: I bought my first computer programming book in 1977 while I was still in High School. At the time, my school didn't even have a computer class. After I graduated from high school, I served my country for 4 years in the Air Force. After I completed my term of enlistment, I went to the California Polytechnic State University in San Luis Obispo to study Computer Science. I have been programming computers professionally since 1986. During my career as a software engineer I have worked at a variety of companies to grow my skill in software development. The companies I have worked for include: Lockheed, Compaq, Hewlett-Packard, Digital Video Systems, Flight Safety, and NASA.
